    <div class="card fade-in">
        <div class="card-header">Help Page for secNET</div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <div class="help-section" id="introduction-to-secnet">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-book"></i> 1. Introduction to secNET</h2>
                <p>
                    secNET is a security management application designed to help Control Room Operators (CROs) monitor staff compliance with company policies, rules, health and safety procedures, and regulations using a checklist system. Managers/Supervisors review these checklists, while Admins manage users and system settings. The application supports efficient oversight and reporting across branches for Woermann Brock & Co. Pty. Ltd.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="help-section" id="cro-instructions">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-video"></i> 2. CRO Instructions and Procedures</h2>
                <p>CROs are responsible for monitoring staff via the CCTV system and completing compliance checklists during their shifts. Follow these steps:</p>
                <h3>Logging In</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Open secNET in your browser.</li>
                    <li>Enter your username and password.</li>
                    <li>If assigned to a specific branch, select your branch during login.</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Completing the CCTVLog Checklist</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>From the main dashboard, click "Application" on the top navigation bar and click "CCTVLog" in the dropdown.</li>
                    <li>Enter your name and surname.</li>
                    <li>Select the date of your shift.</li>
                    <li>Choose the shift type (e.g., morning, afternoon, night).</li>
                    <li>Complete the checklist during your shift, answering questions related to company code of conduct, rules, health, and safety procedures.</li>
                    <li>At the end of your shift, click Submit Checklist.</li>
                </ol>
                <p class="important-notes"><strong>Important Notes:</strong></p>
                <ul class="important-notes">
                    <li>For any question answered "No," provide a comment including who, what, when, and where.</li>
                    <li>Only one submission is allowed per CRO per shift (maximum 2 reports per branch per day).</li>
                    <li>Use the Operator Notes field to add additional or critical information.</li>
                    <li>Contact the on-duty supervisor immediately if you encounter technical issues.</li>
                    <li>Report major or serious misconduct or incidents to your supervisor immediately—do not wait until the end of your shift.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="help-section" id="managers-instructions">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-users-cog"></i> 3. Managers/Supervisors Instructions and Procedures</h2>
                <p>Managers and Supervisors review submitted CCTVLog checklists, ensuring compliance and taking action where needed. Follow these steps:</p>
                <h3>Logging In</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Follow the same login steps as CROs.</li>
                    <li>If you manage multiple branches, you may have broader access depending on your role (Tier 2 or Tier 3).</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Reviewing CCTVLog Checklists</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>From the main dashboard, click "Application" on the top navigation bar and click "Review CCTVLogs" in the dropdown.</li>
                    <li>Select the branch to review (available to Admins only for branch selection).</li>
                    <li>Choose a submitted CCTVLog to review.</li>
                    <li>Provide action taken details in the designated fields for any question answered "No."</li>
                    <li>Enter your name and surname at the bottom of the page.</li>
                    <li>Select the date of submission.</li>
                    <li>Click Submit Review.</li>
                </ol>
                <p class="important-notes"><strong>Important Notes:</strong></p>
                <ul class="important-notes">
                    <li>For any "No" answer, the action taken must include who, what, when, and where.</li>
                    <li>All reviews must be completed daily to ensure accurate data, avoid backlogs, and maintain workflow.</li>
                    <li>Contact the on-duty Admin immediately if you experience technical issues.</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Managing Incident Reports</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>From the main dashboard, click "Application" on the top navigation bar and click "Report Explorer" in the dropdown.</li>
                    <li>Filter reports by date, type, or status.</li>
                    <li>Review details and take action (e.g., assign to a team member or close the report).</li>
                </ol>
                <h3>Generating Reports</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>In Report Explorer, select filters (e.g., date range, branch).</li>
                    <li>Choose a report type (e.g., compliance summary, incident report).</li>
                    <li>Click Generate and export the report in HTML format.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="help-section" id="admin-instructions">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-user-shield"></i> 4. Admin Instructions and Procedures</h2>
                <p>Admins (Tier 3 users) manage the system and users. Here’s how to perform your key tasks:</p>
                <h3>Logging In</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Log in with your admin credentials. You’ll have full access to all branches and settings.</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>User Management</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Go to the Admin page (in navigation bar on top of page).</li>
                    <li>
                        To add a user:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Click Add User, enter their details, and assign a role (Tier 1: CRO, Tier 2: Manager/Supervisor, Tier 3: Admin).</li>
                            <li>Assign branch(es) if applicable.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>To edit or remove a user, select their profile and update or delete as needed.</li>
                </ol>
                <h3>System Configuration</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>On the Admin page, access Settings.</li>
                    <li>Adjust system-wide options (e.g., log retention period, notification settings).</li>
                    <li>Save changes to apply them across all branches.</li>
                </ol>
                <h3>Monitoring and Auditing</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Use Report Explorer to view audit logs.</li>
                    <li>Track changes to users, logs, or incidents for security oversight.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="help-section" id="features">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-tools"></i> 5. Features</h2>
                <p>This section explains secNET’s key features and how they benefit users.</p>
                <h3>CCTVLog</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong class="checklist-item p strong">What it does:</strong> Enables CROs to monitor staff compliance with company policies, rules, and safety procedures using a checklist.</li>
                    <li><strong class="checklist-item p strong">How to use it:</strong> Enter your name, select date and shift type, complete the checklist during your shift, and submit at the end.</li>
                    <li><strong class="checklist-item p strong">Benefit:</strong> Ensures consistent monitoring and documentation of staff adherence to standards.</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Incident Report Creator</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong class="checklist-item p strong">What it does:</strong> Allows users to document "General", "Criminal", and "Policy Violation" incidents.</li>
                    <li><strong class="checklist-item p strong">How to use it:</strong> Input incident details then submit. Data will be captured in the database and report copy will be created in the "Documents" folder.</li>
                    <li><strong class="checklist-item p strong">Benefit:</strong> Standardizes incident reporting and tracks resolution.</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Review CCTVLogs</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong class="checklist-item p strong">What it does:</strong> Allows Managers/Supervisors to review and approve CCTVLog checklists.</li>
                    <li><strong class="checklist-item p strong">How to use it:</strong> Select a branch (Admin privilege), review submissions, add action taken for "No" answers, and submit.</li>
                    <li><strong class="checklist-item p strong">Benefit:</strong> Maintains oversight and ensures corrective actions are documented.</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Report Explorer</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong class="checklist-item p strong">What it does:</strong> Provides search, filter, and report generation tools.</li>
                    <li><strong class="checklist-item p strong">How to use it:</strong> Search logs or incidents, apply filters, and export reports.</li>
                    <li><strong class="checklist-item p strong">Benefit:</strong> Simplifies access to compliance data and supports audits.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

